ll be recognized at an awards ceremony and luncheon to be held at the Jefferson Hotel in Richmond Feb  19  2015  Given each year since 1986  the Outstanding Faculty Awards recognize excellence in teaching  research  and service  Recipients are selected based upon their contributions to their students  academic disciplines  institutions  and communities  This year s recipients were selected from among 88 nominees  Turner and Moore are the first VMI faculty members to receive this award since Dr  Duncan Richter  professor of English  rhetoric and humanistic studies  was honored in 2008  After a successful career in biomedical research  medical education  and administration  Turner returned to VMI full time in 2001  From 2001 to 2009  he served as VMI s founding director of undergraduate research  Since 2009  Turner has chaired the biology department  and he currently holds the title of Beverly M  Read  41 Institute Professor in the Arts and Sciences  In 2013  he became the founding chair of the VMI service committee  In the community  Turner has been a longtime member of the Lexington chapter of Rotary International  He s also made many efforts to offer enrichment opportunities in science education to elementary and middle school students in Lexington and Rockbridge County  Over the years  Turner has been the recipient of numerous awards  among them the 2014 Jackson Hope Prize for Excellence in Academic Achievement  He is one of the few VMI alumni or faculty who are two time recipients of the Virginia Military Institute Achievement Medal for exceptional service  In the nomination  Turner was lauded by the many cadets and alumni he s mentored over the years for his constant devotion to each cadet s personal and professional development  Also supporting the nomination was Brig  Gen  Jeffrey G  Smith Jr   79  deputy superintendent for academics and dean of the faculty  He wrote   In a school known for developing citizen scholars of the highest caliber  Dr  Jim Turner represents Virginia Military Institute s finest example of the inspirational role model for cadets in their formative years   He is the complete educator  inspirational teacher  gifted administrator  ground breaking researcher  and spiritual leader    He is widely cited in student and peer surveys as that once in a generation educator who transforms lives  Moore  who s been teaching at VMI since 2010  was praised for his extensive and ongoing efforts to help cadets bridge the gap between the classroom and the world of practice as professional engineers  In recognition of this  Moore was awarded VMI s Jackson Hope Teaching Award in 2011  In particular  Moore was recognized for his creation of two unique programs  The Field to Forum program  which  working with the Department of English  Rhetoric  and Humanistic Studies  has the goal of producing professionally prepared engineers capable of explaining their research successfully to multiple audiences  The second initiative  VMI Clean Energy and Air Resources Program  uses hands on research in the environmental analysis of alternative energy and sustainable fuel development  The CLEAR program is noted for its cutting edge use of manure based biochars for drinking water filtration  a project that could save lives in developing countries  Moore has been recognized for his leadership of Keydets Without Borders  a service group he founded shortly after arriving at VMI as a faculty member  Over the past few years  Moore has led dozens of cadets to the small mountain village of Pampoyo  Bolivia  where Keydets Without Borders has not only installed a safe water system but also has begun a project to bring indoor plumbing to each family in the village  Infant mortality in Pampoyo has dropped by almost 55 percent since the group began its efforts  In addition  Keydets Without Borders has completed several projects in the United States  and has also worked in Haiti and Uganda  The group now has more than 150 members from both VMI and neighboring Washington and Lee University  Support for Moore s application for the Outstanding Faculty Award came from individuals on two continents   Dr  Moore and his team are like angels sent from heaven to provide us with clean  drinkable water  said Florencio Condori  mayor and chief elder of Pampoyo  Bolivia   His tireless efforts have brought life back to our village  and hope back to our hearts  Also recognizing Moore s contributions to both the VMI community and the wider world was Gen  J H  Binford Peay III  62  Institute superintendent   Besides the very clear demonstrated excellence in the art of teaching to our young cadets  Dr  Moore has also shown strong personal and professional qualities while undertaking a myriad of duties  said Peay   Without reservation  Dr  Moore is a superstar and a stalwart in his field  An instructor of the highest character  he cares deeply for people and his students  The OFA program is administered by SCHEV and funded by a grant from the Dominion Foundation  which has fully supported the OFA program since 2005  Since the first awards ceremony in 1987  341 Virginia faculty members  including the 2015 recipients  have received this honor   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 